<p class="header noPspace" dir="ltr">Special Events</p>
<p class="noPspace" dir="ltr">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="noPspace" dir="ltr">ADOPTIVE &amp; FOSTER PARENT WORKSHOP: Becoming a Trauma Competent Healing Parent</p>
<p class="noPspace" dir="ltr">Saturday, February 22, 2014</p>
<p class="noPspace" dir="ltr">9am-12pm at Crossroads Oakley</p>
<p class="noPspace" dir="ltr">Join us for a workshop examining how to become "trauma competent healing parents." During the workshop, participants will be coached on these three essential skills:</p>
<p class="noPspace" dir="ltr">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="noPspace" dir="ltr">- How to maximize a child&rsquo;s sense of felt safety</p>
<p class="noPspace" dir="ltr">- How to help a child manage overwhelming emotions</p>
<p class="noPspace" dir="ltr">- How to help a child with difficult behaviors</p>
<p class="noPspace" dir="ltr">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="noPspace" dir="ltr">The workshop will be led by&nbsp;<a href="http://jayneschooler.blogspot.com/">Jayne and David Schooler</a>&nbsp;who have been active in orphan ministry for more than 25 years encouraging and training adoptive and foster families and advocating for the fatherless across the world.</p>
<p class="noPspace" dir="ltr">Childcare is provided for infants through 5th grade by advance registration only.</p>
<p class="noPspace" dir="ltr"><a href="https://www.surveymonkey.com/s/schooler">Click here to register for this event by Saturday, February 15.</a></p>
<p class="noPspace" dir="ltr">&nbsp;</p>
